			Go through the midst of the city,
			through the midst of Jerusalem,
			and set a mark <span class="hebrew at-red">תָּו</span> upon the foreheads of the men
			that sigh and that cry for all the abominations
			that be done in the midst thereof
		</p>
	</div>

	<br />

	<div class="card-header"><h5 class="text-center">Ezekiel 9:5-6</h5></div>
	<div class="card-body">
		<p class="lead text-center">
			<sup><b class="text-primary">5</b></sup> And to the others he said in mine hearing, Go ye after him through the city,
			and smite: let not your eye spare, neither have ye pity: 
			<sup><b class="text-primary">6</b></sup> Slay utterly old and young, both maids, and little children, and women:
			but come not near any man upon whom is the mark <span class="hebrew at-red">תָּו</span>; and begin at my sanctuary.
		</p>
